title: Orlando Furioso
creator: Ludovico Ariosto
description: LibriVox recording of Orlando Furioso, by Ludovico Ariosto, translated by John Harington. Read by Thomas A. Copeland. Charlemagne's nephew Orlando (AKA Roland) is driven insane by the infidelity of his beloved Angelica. Angelica's relationship with him and others loosely unifies multiple story lines to produce a rich tapestry of romance, fictionalized history, and pure fantasy. This romance-epic is a sequel to the less distinguished and unfinished romance Orlando Innamorato, by Mattteo Maria Boiardo. (Summary by Thomas A. Copeland) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats or languages (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobook; epic poetry; Adventure, Erotica, Fantasy, Myths/Legends, Tragedy;
